A. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design Low-Level Design for Elevator System.

Requirements:

Multiple elevators in a building with multiple floors.
Users can call the elevator from any floor (up/down request).
Inside the elevator, users can press floor buttons.
Elevator should efficiently serve requests (move up/down, stop at requested floors).
Support multiple elevators working together.
Handle basic scenarios like door open/close, emergency stop (simplified).
Show current floor and direction of each elevator.

Constraints:

In-memory implementation is fine.
Focus on core elevator movement and request handling.
Support concurrency (multiple users requesting at same time).

Edge Cases:

Elevator is full.
Requests in both directions.
No requests (elevator should go to idle state).
Invalid floor request.

B. HAPPY PATH STORY

=> Sachin lives on the 12th floor. He presses the Down button on the 12th floor.
=> The system assigns the nearest available elevator (Elevator A on 8th floor)
=> Elevator A arrives at 12th floor, doors open. Sachin enters and presses Ground floor.
=> The elevator stops at any intermediate floors if other users have requested them, then reaches the ground floor.
=> Doors open, Sachin exits, and the elevator becomes available again.
=> This covers: External request → Elevator assignment → Internal floor selection → Movement → Completion.

C. 6 MANDATORY STEPS FOR LLD DESIGN

1. Clarify requirements

=> Functional: Call elevator from floor, select destination inside, efficient movement, multiple elevators.
=> Non-Functional: Minimize waiting time, handle concurrent requests.
=> Assumptions: Single building, simple distance-based assignment, doors and emergency are simplified.
=> Edge Cases: Elevator full, conflicting direction requests, idle elevator positioning.

2. Identify entities and relationships

=> Main entities : Building, Elevator, FloorRequest, ElevatorRequest, ElevatorController
=> Key relationships :
Building has multiple Elevators
Elevator has current floor, direction, and list of requests
ElevatorController manages all elevators and assigns requests

