E. POSSIBLE FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS FROM INTERVIEWER (WITH ANSWER)

Q1. How do you choose the best elevator?
Answer: Simple logic based on distance. In advanced systems, we use direction matching + load balancing.

Q2. How do you handle multiple requests efficiently?
Answer: Each elevator maintains a sorted set of stops (TreeSet).
This allows efficient movement in one direction before reversing.

Q3. What if all elevators are busy?
Answer: We can add a queue for pending requests and assign when an elevator becomes free.